{"amendments":[{"body":"Remove the legacy-schema compatibility and repair paths; they directly contradict the task contract and weaken validation. `TaskRunEntry` still accepts missing linkage metadata through optional/defaulted fields (`src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs:275-298`), `read_task_runs_from_path` silently backfills a missing `milestone_id` instead of rejecting the row (`src/adapters/fs.rs:2536-2558`), and completion journal parsing/repair still accepts and rewrites legacy delimited payloads (`src/adapters/fs.rs:2283-2313`, `src/adapters/fs.rs:2424-2459`). The prompt explicitly says there is no old on-disk data and these migration/backfill paths should be removed, so shipping them means malformed new writes will be hidden instead of failing fast.","rationale":"This is both a requirements miss and a robustness problem: the new self-contained schema is no longer enforced at read time."},{"body":"Fix start-attempt matching so it distinguishes a real retry from an idempotent replay. `find_matching_running_task_run` ignores its `started_at` parameter entirely (`src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs:416-442`), and `record_task_run_start` then either reuses any sole runless open row or appends a second row when the retry arrives with a newly known `run_id` (`src/adapters/fs.rs:2815-2856`). That makes the audit trail wrong in both directions: a genuine second retry without `run_id` is silently collapsed into the first attempt, while a replay of the same logical attempt that now has a `run_id` leaves behind a phantom `Running` row forever. The current behavior is even codified in `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:3179-3235`.","rationale":"The feature is supposed to answer 'what happened to bead X?'; with this matching logic, retry history can be either lost or duplicated depending on when `run_id` becomes available."}],"summary":"Working-tree `git diff` was empty, so I reviewed the current milestone-record implementation directly and found 2 issues. The main problems are retained legacy-schema/backfill logic that the task explicitly forbids, and retry matching that misrecords attempts when `run_id` is absent or appears later. `cargo test milestone_record -- --nocapture` passes, so these are logic/contract issues rather than uncovered test failures."}